  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "d1aefe31-44ca-485d-a16e-5f21262f62b2",
    "name": "Pika Labs via fal.ai Queue API",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": {
      "content": "Pika Labs does not publish a first-party REST API on its main domain.\nProduction REST access to Pika's video generation models is provided\nthrough the fal.ai inference platform's standard Queue API.\n\nSubmit an inference request with POST /{model_id}, then poll\nGET /{model_id}/requests/{request_id}/status (or stream it) until the\nrequest completes, and fetch the result with\nGET /{model_id}/requests/{request_id}. Authentication is a fal.ai API\nkey sent as `Authorization: Key $FAL_KEY`.\n\nThe {model_id} path component identifies a specific Pika model on fal.ai\n(for example `fal-ai/pika`). Only the generic Queue API surface is\nmodeled here; see the fal.ai documentation under externalDocs for\nmodel-specific input and output schemas.\n\n\nContact Support:\n Name: fal.ai documentation",
      "type": "text/plain"
    }
  }
